Well this past week I went to Las Vegas for the very first time and I was lucky enough to get the opportunity to celebrate the 4th of July with my American neighbours! I found Las Vegas to be such an inspirational city. I was able to transform this inspiration into musical creativity and I came up with the massive set that I have been promising you guys, Live in Vegas! I hope everyone enjoys my hard work and I really look forward to hearing everybody’s thoughts and comments - don't be shy! Also on a side note, my album art is a picture I took of Vegas from the plane, pretty cool!

Cheers,
-Jade

origin.description:
There’s a beating heart buried in the cold landscape of Glider, a warm 4/4 pulse that enervates the album’s echoing, looped drones and pulls the listener swiftly through the snow. By pinning barely-there electronic beats to his wisps of guitar melody, the Seattle-based producer turns ambient music into a hybrid strain of breathtakingly intimate, small-scale dance music.

There’s a separation of elements in The Sight Below’s songs that’s almost meteorological in nature: Tendrils of treated guitar trail lazy patterns in the sky like the Aurora Borealis (“At First Touch”), flicker in the distance like heat lightning (“Dour”), or expand and contract like time-lapse cloud formations (“Life’s Fading Light”); running along beneath, nearly obscured by the airborne phenomena, is an ever-present beat, which ranges from the mud-puddle throb in “Without Motion” to the tiny, insistent high-hats in “A Fractured Smile.” The tracks evolve at a deliberated pace, but as the tones overlap and the rhythms build, time oozes to a halt and hangs in blissfully frost-bitten suspended animation.

With Glider, The Sight Below has created a work of vertiginous sonic depth and exquisite melancholy: techno music for a dark, brooding night.

NOTE: The vinyl version is a different tracklist from the original CD/Digital version of GLIDER. Also, the 2xLP format comes in a 4-panel gatefold jacket with a matte finish and includes a download card of the digital bonus version. The digital bonus version stays true to the original Glider tracklist plus compiles early EP material and an unreleased remix by Eluvium.

Release details here: http://ghostly.com/releases/glider-lp-version-+-digital-bonus-version

Find it in the Ghostly Store: (coming soon)

origin.description: This is a welcome message for the http://soundsoffringe.com map.  SoundCloud will be going to Edinburgh fringe festival.  We want anyone interested in getting involved to post audio during the festival and plot it to his sound map using the iPhone or Android app!  You could record a joke, an interview, banter, chit chat, backstage gossip or even just sounds from the streets.  Simply enter 'fringe' into the title of your audio and then make sure to select 'where' in the upload options and select your location - it will then get plotted to the map!

track.description:
This month we have a rather fabulous guest mix from London's simply splendid Sean Johnston, better known as Hardway Bros or as the other half responsible for Andrew Weatheralls seminal night A love from Outer Space. The show traverses the wide abyss that is all things electronic this month with tracks from Bonobo, 40 winks, paralell dance ensemble, red rack em, beaumont, Jonno Mccleery, belleruche, appollo brown, flako, dynas, mux mool, bonobo, malachai, ossie, dionigi, moniker and john tejada. Handing over the reigns to sean with a stupendously slick mix of raw and ready house and electronica. It's bigger than big.....it's extra large : )

Take some time to listen, share with friends family, random strangers and anyone else who would like a few hours of musical meanderings... For info and details on shows join the Reframe Facebook page for irregular mailouts minus the spam. Includes tracklistings and a place to ponder questions. You can join here - http://www.facebook.com/group.php?gid=104474882918132

It’s a brief switch up with Sub Focus and the unmistakable sound of Junior Read, classic beats from Lamb and Jake Slazenger, before weaving through Imagination, Jay Z and the lush strings of Love Unlimited Orchestra. origin.description:
Irk's back, and this time he's on a dubstep, grime and hiphop mission, with this special collaboration mix for Solid Steel and Montreal's bassmusic podcast J'aime Le Dubstep. We kick off with a few serious UK sounds from Durrty Goodz and BeggarFam, then hit some swirling electronic heaviness from Matta and Siriusmo. Next it's over to the hiphop for fresh Raekwon and Beasties, plus pure wonkiness from Eprom and South London's KeepUp! crew. And finally back to more beats and bass from the likes of Culprate and Pinch & Roska, plus Kid Koala's The Slew project, Wick-It's Black Keys refix and a familiar Bristol beat right at the end to tie it all up.

Phreek Plus One are Italy’s most kept secret luminaries in the world of disco. They don’t play at Berlusconi’s secret VIP partys, but they like the Bunga Bunga funk. All in here. Well, they are also associated with jazz, in fact they are jazz connoisseurs and rare record collectors, and approved selectors, as a matter of coursetop Italien mix DJs. Well, they are musicians, too, but never played the dodgy Italian Acid Jazz, while they were looking for the real cool good Baia Degli Angeli vibe,in fact they are at least inspired by Garage House, soulful 70ties and 80ties disco, Cosmic, Funk, Soul and Jazz.
Their previous released four EPs on Compost Black Label gained really cult status, while some tunes (for example like „Bikini“) caused a fuss on the underground disco circuit and their 12“ are still in demand, heavily played by Harvey, Gerd Janson, Pete Herbert, Tim Sweeney, Chateau Flight, Deetron, Tensnake, Holy Ghost, Sleazy McQueen, Anthony Mansfield, Permanent Vacation, Munk, Pete Tong, Ray Mang, Maurice Fulton and many many others

origin.description:
The legendary DJ Deep has been on the vanguard of house and techno via his Deeply Rooted House imprint as well as essential City to City compilations on BBE and more.

His latest EP under his Mondo guise, titled ‘Work Me Baby’ is out now and features some pure jacking workouts and comes with an excellent Rootstrax mix. 

Clone will also be re-issuing his rare mid 90's collaborative effort alongside Jovonn, entitled ‘Back In The Dark’.

Here, he comes correct with a mix of upfront house and techno.

For DJ Deep bookings please email bookings@uzuriartistbookingsandmanagement.com
